- Performance rankings refer to the player's standing within their team based on points, rebounds, and assists per game in descending order; 
- Access frequency refers to the number of times a player's data has been accessed by users; 
- Recent access logs are considered to be those from within the last month, which is assumed to be 30 days for simplicity; 
- Detailed statistics include points per game, rebounds per game, assists per game, steals per game, blocks per game, three-point percentage, free-throw percentage, and field goal percentage.

